description:
The new ongoing series starring Tefe Holland, daughter of comics' original Swamp Thing reveals new secrets about the young elemental. Tefe Holland is back, and her elemental blood has drawn her back into the Green, a realm she was born to rule, but one her half-human mind barely recognizes. While Tefe takes the tour to its shocking conclusion, Abby Arcane, unaware her daughter is alive, tells a bone-chilling tale of how her search for Tefe reunited the world's greatest couple in joy, blood, and a desperate, magical pact.

Notes:

  • The cover is a homage of the Pieta.
name: A Tree Falls in the Forest

description: As the new Swamp God travels in search of her destiny, this new ongoing series sprouts intriguing twists and tangles. When a killer storm gathers over subzero Alaskan waters, one member of a crab boat's crew decides to take control of their collective destiny. One of the witnesses to the ensuing tragedy is Tefe Holland. It's a chilling confrontation with human nature for the new half-human Swamp God; will she intervene...and if so, how?

As Tefe continues to explore her powers and her purpose, she has to make an agonizing decision, bringing her face to face with both sides of her heritage. She must choose whether to save a human family or an elder from the Green as a forest fire rages out of control. Also, meet Barnabas, a horribly scarred Inuit with a mysterious past.

description: The start of a new storyline serves as the perfect jumping-on point for new readers! When Tefe finds a flyer for a band called Arcane, she and Barnabas head to New York City to find out how the band may be connected to her uncle, Anton Arcane. There, a horrific series of events forces Tefe to confront the possibility that she is truly heir to the evil that is Arcane. Meanwhile, the Department of Agriculture intensifies its search for Tefe.

description: The penultimate chapter of this epic storyline has all of the players arriving in Los Angeles. Tefé and Heather plan to assassinate Senator Strand; Agent Romero has kidnapped the Conways; Kudzu is trying to assassinate Tefé; and Kilroy and Agent Orange are set on stopping him. When the smoke clears, more than one person's life may be over.

description: The conclusion to the 7-part "Red Harvest." In the finale, all the threads of the past year converge into an explosive showdown. Tefe tries to rescue her foster parents, the Conways, from psychotic killer Romero. We discover the truth about Heather's father, Senator Strand. The secret identity of the DDI Director who's been trailing Tefe for a year is revealed. And the final fates of several members of the cast are decided. And finally, can the original Swamp Thing let all this go by without making an appearance?
name: Red Harvest Conclusion: Topiary

description: In this issue, two legends return: essential Swamp Thing artist John Totleben paints the cover, and the original Swamp Thing returns to confront Tefé over her deeds. Tefé counters him with an even more pointed question: If Swamp Thing is a god, why doesn't he try to end human suffering? In this emotional story, the true purpose of both Swamp Thing and Tefé will be revealed.
name: Last of the Loose Ends

description: Tefé's search for the Tree of Knowledge heats up! Journeying to Africa with Pilate, she meets an African medicine woman who agrees to take Tefé to the Tree. But first Tefé must atone for her past sins and ask permission from the continent's ancestors.
name: Rootless
